Description:
Tranquil family living
Nestled in the quiet yet amenity filled township of Lang Lang situates this gorgeous family home that oozes light and character throughout. Boasting a large allotment with plenty of yard space for all the family to appreciate.
- Updated kitchen with quality finishes & appliances
- Huge 9x5m undercover alfresco decked out in Merbau which comes complete with Coonara wood fire heater & TV included
- Quiet location with generous block size
- Additional features include ducted heating, split system, tinted windows, solar panels, large side access driveway. Plus bonus massive 13x8m machinery shed with fully sealed concrete floor, 15amp + 3 phase available, double roller door with 4.3m clearance & extra rear roller door with laneway access
Ideally located within walking distance to all amenities the village has to offer including shops, brewery, Lang Lang Primary School, public transport, Western Port Hwy and major road arterials.

Description:
Seaside Escape with Glimpses of Bay!!
Upon driving up to this property the appeal from the front with colonial windows and charming verandahs creates an inviting feeling to inspect. Upon entering the home you will be welcomed by a spacious light filled living area, good size modern kitchen with plenty of room for dining/meals table and has sliding door opening onto deck area, easy maintenance flooring, 2 bedrooms with BIR and wwc, split-system air conditioning , family bathroom with spa bath and separate shower, laundry with bench space and there is a cloak room for those muddy boots and wet coats. Upstairs offers master with walk-in-robe and en-suite. The property has been freshly painted and refurbished throughout and is fully fenced and has a good size family friendly backyard and garden shed. Pioneer Bay is only approx. 112 kms to CBD with dual lane highway for easy commute, local shops with permanent doctor, chemist, bank, ambulance depot, cafes, v-line service approx. 4 mins there is a school bus near the entry of Pioneer Bay, major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx. 25 mins.

Description:
Character Family Home with a Development opportunity!
With all the space in the world here we have on offer a freshly painted beautifully presented 3 bedroom 2 bathroom recently renovated home. Just like a new home but with that comfortable character feel & all set on a generous block 892m2 approx. (17.74m x 50.29m)
Appealing from the moment you enter the front door, this home is light & bright with large windows through-out.Featuring a formal dining room with a lovely high ornate ceiling & gas heater, the spacious modern kitchen is bright & welcoming and then thru to a large lounge room with a charming wood heater & air conditioning. The master bedroom includes a tastefully renovated ensuite & the remaining 2 double bedrooms also have BIR's & quality carpets. The rear of the property offers a covered outdoor deck area with garages and shedding, is fully fenced with plenty of room for a large family and potential for a dual occupancy (STCA).

Description:
Picturesque Period Style Home – Welcome to 14 The Esplanade
Attention – All serious renovators, owners, occupiers and investors!
Built in 1910, this beloved home is characterized by its charming facade, situated on approximately 711m of land and has all the necessary ingredients for a stunning 21st century transformation, or ( STCA ) Build and start again.
Positioned north – facing capturing Western Port and French Island views.
The current interior comprises 2-3 bedrooms, central lounge and dining area, kitchen, bathroom, laundry area. Garage, and garden shed.
With charm and romance of yesteryear, this quintessential “renovator’s delight” is now waiting for the next chapter of its story to unfold.
This thriving community offers a great lifestyle including great tourist events, Penguin parade, local vineyards and much more and is only 40 minutes to the world-famous GP track.
This truly is an opportunity not to be missed.
Daniel & Tamara from @realty Bass Coast have the pleasure of presenting this magnificent property in Corinella.

Description:
Lifestyle with Amazing Bay Views
With expansive views of the water, this ultra-modern double storey 2 bedroom + study home is open, airy and full of light. Nestled in a quiet pocket of Corinella set back from the main thoroughfare you can relax and enjoy the breathtaking sunsets, the beautiful bird life & the gentle sound of water lapping the beach. Follow the walking tracks to the beach & only moments to the 24 hour jetty for fishing & boating. All living areas are upstairs to take advantage of these incredible views over looking the water to the San Remo Bridge Philip Island & also French Island.
Features include: A substantial balcony with stunning views, fabulous new kitchen, polished floorboards upstairs, polished concrete floors on the ground level reduce heat in summer & a stunning bathroom which brings the outside in with its fernery. The home offers additional power rooms both upstairs and down.
This beautiful home is sure to delight, contact the agent now to arrange an inspection.

Floating timber flooring, sliding door out to a double carport, with built in cupboards. New carpet in lounge and bedrooms, master has WIR and ensuite. 2nd bathroom has spa bath. Ducted vacuum system throughout the home.
Modern kitchen including dishwasher, pot drawers, 2 pantries, 900mm oven and 5 burner gas cook top and plenty of bench space, with overhead cupboards.

Description:
Excellent Buy and here's why!
This beautifully presented home comprises 3 double bedrooms plus study or 4th bedroom. This home is a delight to inspect offering a large L shaped lounge & dining room with split system air con. & wood heater to take care of your year round comfort. Featuring an excellent well appointed kitchen open to a large family/meals area with dble sliding glass doors for entry onto the back timber deck & established low maintenance garden. The master bedroom has an ensuite and an enormous WIR, the main bathroom offers a bath, sep shower & toilet, plus there's a sep. laundry all set on fully fenced block of 548m2 approx. The garage with roller door is large enough for a big workshop as well as the car and there is also solar system on the roof. This is a lovely home in a seaside village, close to V-Line bus and an easy drive to Phillip Island, an inspection will delight.

Peace, Tranquility and a Lifestyle to Cherish!

Very Well Presented Property

New 12mm laminate flooring and new carpet, in an open plan living area. Modern kitchen, electric stove top and oven with overhead cupboards. Description:
HUGE BLOCK! WONDERFUL FAMILY HOME IN AN IDEAL LOCATION
Beautifully presented country cottage sitting on an amazing - 1600m block approx. If you have been looking for a home that offers beach country style living or just need a weekender and somewhere to retreat to from the hustle & bustle of everyday life you will not find better than this timeless beauty in Tenby Point.
Bright & comfortable, neat & tidy, Plenty of living space & generous bedrooms x3 and 2 of the bedrooms have BIR, great size main bathroom and large laundry, kitchen offers plenty of storage, dish washer, family area with wood fire. The home also offers a great sun room with a warm and inviting north facing veranda that holds a spot for a comfy chair for the morning sunshine in the summer and the afternoon warmth in the winter. There is a large lock up garage, plenty of room for a large boat and caravan on the property as well, and the beach is just at the end of the srteet.
Please call Tamara & Daniel

Description:
Serenity and ideal location
This well-appointed family home is on a generous block of approximately 1,381m2 and set in a tranquil yet accessible location.
Showcasing 3 generous size bedrooms with built in robes, master with walk-in robe and full en-suite with his/her vanities and double size shower, 2 living zones, spacious open plan kitchen with stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, pendant drop lights and walk in pantry and has convenient access from family/meals area to entertainment deck. Other features include large floor tiles, well equipped laundry, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, wood heater with feature wall, extra-large double garage with remote control door and rear roller access through to the backyard as well as internal access.
The spacious backyard lends itself to large shed, inground pool and landscaped gardens creating the perfect serenity and ideal location to appreciate beautiful sunsets. Only a stone’s throw to the water, minutes to 24-hour boat ramp, local primary school, kindergarten, doctor, chemist, bank, ambulance depot and cafes are all within 7kms and major shopping centre and Phillip Island approximately 25 mins.

Description:
IMMACULATE MODERN STYLE HOME IN THE HEART OF GRANTVILLE
Set within a scenic country town of Grantville, this charming home with country views has a comfortable & spacious open plane kitchen area with breakfast bar & dining area. There are 2 family living areas in the home both with reverse cycle heating and cooling and a woodfire in one.
Featuring 4 bedrooms all with BIR’s & master with walk in robe, generous main bathroom, large laundry. Loads of storage throughout the home, including an entertaining deck.
The home sits on a 981m block approx. and was only built approximately 2 years ago.
The property is tucked away from it all but conveniently surrounded by all amenities including Beach Trails, Public Transport, Cafes, Shops, Medical services & much more.
Easy access to some of the best schools in Bass Coast - Bass Valley Primary School and the new Early Childhood campus and all Secondary Schools in the surrounding areas.
This thriving community offers a great life style including great tourist events, Penguin parade, local vine yards and much more and is only 40 Minutes to the world-famous GP track.
This property is a must see if you are looking for a relaxed coastal rural life style. Located in the heart of the township of Grantville.
